America. The lyrics come from "Defence of Fort M'Henry", a poem written on 
September 14, 1814, by the 35-year-old lawyer and amateur poet Francis Scott 
Key after witnessing the bombardment of Fort McHenry by ... During the 
bombardment, HMS Erebus provided the "rockets' red glare".
